# Write the commit message in the first line, following the format:
#
# [status]:[type]: [description]

# Status: can be "DONE" (task completed) or "WIP" (work in progress)
# Type: can be "feat" (new feature), "fix" (bug fix), "refactor" (code improvement), "docs" (documentation), "test" (testing), etc.
# Description: should be brief and explain the purpose of the commit
# Examples of commit messages:
# DONE feat: add function to sum two numbers
# WIP:refactor: improve code readability
# DONE:docs: update README.md with usage instructions
